    640          /***************************************************************************//**
    641           * @brief
    642           *   Configure the USART operating in synchronous mode to use a given baudrate.
    643           *
    644           * @details
    645           *    The configuration will be set to use a bitrate less than or equal to the desired bitrate
    646           *    to ensure that the bitrate does not exceed the requested value.
    647           *
    648           *    For USART peripherals, fractional clock division is suppressed
    649           *    in synchronous mode by this function, even though the hardware allows it.
    650           *    This restriction prevents timing violations causing framing errors and data corruption at high frequencies.
    651           *    The fractional clock division modifies the clock cycles to average out around the desired bitrate,
    652           *    adjusting some half periods clock cycle count.
    653           *    Fractional divider affects the duty cycle of the SCLK, impact is greater at high bitrates where there are few clock cycle count per
    654           *    half period, and can cause timing issues like MISO setup time violations.
